ohn%E2%80%99s%20Railway%20Station%20and%20a%20red%20telephone%20booth%20near%20its%20entrance.%20He%20had%20used%20the%20telephone%20there%20scores%20of%20times.%20His%20ears%20remembered%20the%20clanking%20of%20the%20coins%20falling%20through%20the%20slot.%20The%20steadily%20falling%20snow%20appeared%20less%20than%20white%2C%3Cbr%3E%20discoloured.%20The%20station%20lampposts%20shone%20dim%2C%20much%20dimmer%20than%20usual.%20He%20prayed%20for%20a%20storm%E2%80%94a%20rainstorm%2C%20typhoon%2C%20earthquake%2C%20snowstorm%2C%20any%20storm.%20Anything!%20Something%20to%20wash%20everything%20away.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EAfter%20a%20mysterious%20disappearance%20of%20over%20twenty-four%20hours%2C%20he%20had%20just%20returned%20home.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%E2%80%98Everything%20all%20right%2C%20son%3F%20Can%20I%20come%20in%3F%E2%80%99%20said%20Udho%20after%20knocking%20on%20his%20bedroom%20door%2C%20his%20voice%20muffled.%20Kalu%20heard%20the%20lump%20in%20Udho%E2%80%99s%20throat.%20He%20jumped%20out%20of%20bed%20and%20locked%20the%20door.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%E2%80%98No%2C%20Bhapa.%20I%E2%80%99ll%20see%20you%20in%20the%20morning.%20I%E2%80%99ve%20already%20told%20you%2C%20everything%E2%80%99s%20all%20right%2C%E2%80%99%20he%20said%2C%20clutching%20the%20doorknob%20tightly%20in%20his%20right%20hand.%20His%20head%20touched%20one%20of%20his%20turbans%20hanging%20by%20the%20hook%20on%20the%20door.%20His%20body%20trembled%20as%20he%20turned%20to%20look%20at%20the%20mirror%20on%20the%20dresser.%20He%20thrust%20his%20clenched%20fist%20into%20it.%20The%20mirror%20cracked%2C%20but%20no%20shards%20fell%20off.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%E2%80%98Son%2C%20what%20was%20that%20noise%3F%20Everything%20all%20right%3F%E2%80%99%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EKalu%20put%20his%20hands%20on%20his%20heart%2C%20afraid%20his%20father%20would%20hear%20its%20agitated%20pounding.%20He%20knew%20his%20father%20hadn%E2%80%99t%20believed%20a%20word%20he%20had%20said.%20The%20countless%20fragments%20of%20the%20fractured%20mirror%20reflected%20his%20naked%20body%2C%20dissected%20by%20the%20cracks.%20His%20hands%20moved%20from%20his%20heart%20to%20his%20head.%20The%20touch%20felt%20odd%20to%20his%20hands.%20He%20looked%20into%20the%20mirror%20again.%20It%20showed%20no%20hair%20on%20the%20face%2C%20the%20head%20and%20the%20rest%20of%20the%20body%2C%20except%20at%20the%20crotch%20and%20some%20by%20the%20armpits.%20His%20legs%20wobbled%20under%20him.%20His%20hands%20moved%20to%20feel%20his%20neck%20and%20its%20hairless%20small.%20He%20noticed%20the%20marks%20of%20the%20turban%20on%20his%20forehead.%20His%20facial%20skin%20that%20normally%20hid%20under%20his%20turban%20was%20lighter%20compared%20to%20the%20darker%20brown%20on%20the%20rest%20of%20his%20face.%20The%20black%20birth%20mark%20on%20the%20left%20side%20of%20his%20forehead%20stared%20at%20him%3B%20without%20the%20Sikh%20turban%2C%20the%20hair%20on%20his%20head%20and%20beard%2C%20the%20birth%20mark%20was%20visible%2C%20and%20his%20Chamarhood%20felt%20exposed.%20In%20the%20corner%20of%20his%20eye%2C%20he%20could%20see%20the%20solitary%20bulb%20hanging%20from%20the%20wire%20on%20the%20ceiling.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EHe%20thrust%20his%20fists%20into%20his%20eyes%20and%20turned%20away%20from%20the%20mirror.%20When%20he%20dropped%20his%20fists%2C%20his%20eyes%20opened%20to%20a%20portion%20of%20the%20wall%20above%20the%20headboard.%20Framed%20portraits%20of%20Ravidas%20and%20Ambedkar%2C%20deemed%20deities%20for%20the%20untouchables%2C%20looked%20down%20at%20him.%20In%20the%20dim%20light%20of%20the%20ceiling%20bulb%2C%20they%20looked%20anything%20but%20godlike.%20The%20garlands%20around%20their%20necks%20reeked%20of%20mortality%3B%20like%20nooses%2C%20they%20screamed%20death.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EKalu%E2%80%99s%20eyes%20turned%20to%20the%20small%20framed%20black-and-white%20photo%20of%20Udho%20on%20the%20bedside%20table.%20He%20seemed%20to%20jump%20out%20of%20the%20frame%2C%20dressed%20as%20Kalu%20remembered%20him%20in%201942.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E