's%20chips.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EA%20new%20SEC%20complaint%20alleges%20that%20Musk's%20statement%20is%20false%20based%20on%20research%20records.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EA%20group%20that%20advocates%20for%20ethical%20scientific%20research%20is%20asking%20the%20Securities%20and%20Exchange%20Commission%20to%20investigate%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Felon-musk%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EElon%20Musk%3C%2Fa%3E%20for%20his%20recent%20claim%20that%20no%20monkeys%20have%20died%20as%20a%20result%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fneuralink-elon-musk-microchips-brains-ai-2021-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ENeuralink%3C%2Fa%3E's%20brain%20chip.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Physicians%20Committee%20for%20Responsible%20Medicine%20(PCRM)%2C%20a%20nonprofit%20that%20has%20previously%20lodged%20complaints%20against%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Felon-musk-neuralink-brain-chip-investigated-potential-hazardous-pathogens-monkeys-2023-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ENeuralink's%20conduct%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20asked%20the%20SEC%20in%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.documentcloud.org%2Fdocuments%2F23986937-sec-request-for-investigation-of-neuralink-20230920%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eletter%3C%2Fa%3E%20obtained%20by%20WIRED%20magazine%20to%20investigate%20Musk%20for%20securities%20fraud%20for%20a%20statement%20he%20made%20on%20X%2C%20formerly%20Twitter%2C%20on%20September%2010.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMusk%2C%20who%20co-founded%20the%20biotech%20startup%20in%202016%2C%20wrote%20in%20response%20to%20a%20user%20post%20that%20%26quot%3Bno%20monkey%20has%20died%20as%20a%20result%20of%20a%20Neuralink%20implant%26quot%3B%20%E2%80%94%20a%20chip%20that%20aims%20to%20allow%20humans%20to%20connect%20to%20a%20device%20remotely.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BFirst%20our%20early%20implants%2C%20to%20minimize%20risk%20to%20health%20monkeys%2C%20we%20chose%20terminal%20moneys%20(close%20to%20death%20already)%2C%26quot%3B%20Musk%20wrote%20on%20September%2010%2C%20misspelling%20monkeys.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPCRM%20alleged%20in%20the%20SEC%20letter%20that%20%26quot%3BMusk%20knows%20that%20to%20be%20false.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELast%20year%2C%20PCRM%20revealed%20that%20it%20had%20obtained%20records%20from%20the%20University%20of%20California%2C%20Davis%2C%20where%20Neuralink's%20experiments%20were%20conducted%2C%20that%20they%20said%20showed%20how%20the%20monkeys%20experienced%20%26quot%3B%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Felon-musk-neuralink-experiments-monkeys-extreme-suffering-animal-rights-group-2022-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eextreme%20suffering%3C%2Fa%3E%20as%20a%20result%20of%20inadequate%20animal%20care%20and%20the%20highly%20invasive%20experimental%20head%20implants%20during%20the%20experiments.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDocuments%20and%20research%20notes%20from%20the%20university's%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.pcrm.org%2Fethical-science%2Fanimals-in-medical-research%2Foriginal-records-neuralink%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ECalifornia%20National%20Primate%20Research%20Center%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20were%20published%20on%20PCRM's%20website%20show%20that%20at%20least%20a%20dozen%20monkeys%20that%20had%20chips%20implanted%20experienced%20a%20range%20of%20health%20issues%2C%20including%20infections%20and%20brain%20swelling%2C%20before%20they%20were%20eventually%20euthanized.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOther%20health%20effects%20included%20paralysis%2C%20seizures%2C%20loss%20of%20coordination%20and%20balance%2C%20and%20depression%2C%20PCRM%20wrote%20in%20the%20SEC%20letter.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20experiments%2C%20PCRM%20says%2C%20involved%20an%20hourslong%20surgery%20and%20drilling%20two%20%26quot%3Bdime-sized%26quot%3B%20holes%20in%20the%20side%20of%20the%20monkeys'%20heads%20to%20implant%20the%20device.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%22766%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Neuralink%20brain%20chip%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6269a5ca7f0c1c0018904532%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22738%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ENeuralink%20brain%20chip%3Cp%3ENeuralink%2FYouTube%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20one%20case%2C%20researchers%20noted%20that%20a%206-year-old%20female%20rhesus%20macaque%2C%20labeled%20%26quot%3BAnimal%2015%2C%26quot%3B%20was%20observed%20occasionally%20%26quot%3Bpicking%20or%20even%20pulling%20at%26quot%3B%20the%20implants%20after%20receiving%20the%20surgery%2C%20documents%20showed.%20They%20also%20noted%20other%20behaviors%20such%20as%20possibly%20%26quot%3Bhead%20pressing%26quot%3B%20as%20well%20as%20the%20loss%20of%20balance%20and%20coordination.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOther%20times%2C%20the%20monkey%20would%20also%20hold%20hands%20and%20groom%20her%20%26quot%3Bvisual%20buddy.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20March%202019%2C%20the%20researchers%20noted%20a%20%26quot%3Bcranial%20implant%20infection.%26quot%3B%20Animal%2015%20was%20euthanized%20that%20month%2C%20documents%20showed.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESpokespersons%20for%20Neuralink%20and%20PCRM%20did%20not%20immediately%20respond%20to%20a%20request%20for%20comment.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20group%20also%20objected%20to%20Musk's%20claim%20that%20the%20monkeys%20used%20for%20the%20testing%20were%20%26quot%3Bclose%20to%20death.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BMonkey%20health%20records%20show%20that%2C%20while%20several%20animals%20had%20suffered%20physical%20trauma%20and%20been%20used%20previously%20in%20experiments%20at%20UC%20Davis%2C%20there%20is%20no%20evidence%20that%20they%20were%20'close%20to%20death%2C'%20as%20Musk%20stated%2C%26quot%3B%20PCRM%20wrote%2C%20noting%20that%20the%20rhesus%20macaques%20%26quot%3Boften%20live%20to%20about%2025%20years%20in%20captivity.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20average%20age%20of%20the%20dozen%20monkeys%20that%20died%20during%20Neuralink's%20research%20was%207.25%20years%2C%20the%20group%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20former%20Neuralink%20employee%20who%20requested%20anonymity%20for%20fear%20of%20retaliation%20told%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.wired.com%2Fstory%2Felon-musk-pcrm-neuralink-monkey-deaths%2F%3FredirectURL%3Dhttps%253A%252F%252Fwww.wired.com%252Fstory%252Felon-musk-pcrm-neuralink-monkey-deaths%252F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EWIRED%20magazine%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20Musk's%20claim%20of%20the%20monkeys%20being%20close%20to%20death%20was%20%26quot%3Bridiculous%2C%26quot%3B%20if%20not%20a%20%26quot%3Bstraight%20fabrication.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20employee%20said%20that%20researchers%20needed%20up%20to%20a%20year%20for%20behavioral%20training%20with%20the%20monkeys%20in%20order%20to%20conduct%20Neuralink's%20experiment.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAndy%20Fell%2C%20a%20spokesperson%20for%20the%20University%20of%20California%2C%20Davis%2C%20declined%20to%20provide%20further%20comment%20outside%20of%20the%20school's%20statement%20issued%20last%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BUC%20Davis%20did%20have%20a%20research%20collaboration%20with%20Neuralink%2C%20which%20concluded%20in%202020%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20statement%20said.%20%26quot%3BThe%20research%20protocols%20were%20thoroughly%20reviewed%20and%20approved%20by%20the%20campus's%20Institutional%20Animal%20Care%20and%20Use%20Committee%20(IACUC).%20The%20work%20was%20conducted%20by%20Neuralink%20researchers%20in%20facilities%20at%20the%20California%20National%20Primate%20Research%20Center%20at%20UC%20Davis.%20UC%20Davis%20staff%20provided%20veterinary%20care%20including%20round-the-clock%20monitoring%20of%20experimental%20animals.%20When%20an%20incident%20occurred%2C%20it%20was%20reported%20to%20the%20IACUC%2C%20which%20mandated%20training%20and%20protocol%20changes%20as%20needed.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPCRM%20noted%20in%20the%20letter%20to%20the%20SEC%20that%20Musk%20has%20over%20157%20million%20followers%20on%20X%2C%20%26quot%3Bmeaning%20the%20reach%20of%20his%20messages%20is%20immense%20an