%20researchers%20is%20also%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Ftech%2Ffacebook-services-spread-religious-hatred-wsj-report%5C%22%3Ebelieved%20to%20have%20found%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20WhatsApp%20was%20awash%20with%20%E2%80%9Crumours%20and%20calls%20to%20violence%E2%80%9D%20during%20the%20Delhi%20riots%20of%20February%202020%2C%20with%20some%20users%20saying%20they%20were%20frequently%20subjected%20to%20%E2%80%9Ca%20large%20amount%20of%20content%20that%20encourages%20conflict%2C%20hatred%20and%20violence%20on%20Facebook%20and%20WhatsApp%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EFacebook%20whistleblower%20Frances%20Haugen%2C%20in%20her%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Ftech%2Ffacebook-whistleblower-frances-haugen-complaints-sec-hate-speech-misinformation-india%5C%22%3Ecomplaint%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20the%20US%20Securities%20and%20Exchange%20Commission%2C%20said%20that%20company%20officials%20were%20aware%20of%20the%20structural%20factors%20that%20cause%20the%20spread%20of%20hate%20speech%20and%20harmful%20political%20rhetoric%20on%20its%20platform.%20Her%20complaint%20also%20had%20references%20to%20%E2%80%9Cfear-mongering%E2%80%9D%20content%20promoted%20by%20%E2%80%9CRashtriya%20Swayamsevak%20Sangh%20(RSS)%20users%2C%20groups%20and%20pages%E2%80%9D%20and%20the%20BJP%20IT%20Cell%E2%80%99s%20alleged%20use%20of%20duplicate%20accounts.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EQuestions%20have%20also%20been%20raised%20about%20the%20BJP%E2%80%99s%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.aljazeera.com%2Feconomy%2F2022%2F3%2F14%2Fhow-a-reliance-funded-company-boosts-bjps-campaigns-on-facebook%5C%22%3Epolitical%20advertising%3C%2Fa%3E%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.aljazeera.com%2Feconomy%2F2022%2F3%2F15%2Finside-facebook-and-bjps-world-of-ghost-advertisers%5C%22%3EMeta%20platforms%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3E%E2%80%98Fails%20to%20inspire%20confidence%E2%80%99%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20report%20was%20criticised%20by%20Access%20Now%20as%20failing%20to%20%E2%80%9Cshow%20any%20meaningful%20or%20verifiable%20progress%E2%80%9D%20on%20Meta%CA%BCs%20human%20rights%20harms%20in%20India%20or%20propose%20any%20concrete%20plan%20to%20prepare%20for%20the%202024%20general%20elections.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20digital%20rights%20advocay%20group%20said%20that%20the%20report%20does%20not%20elaborate%20on%20the%20findings%20and%20recommendations%20of%20the%20Human%20Rights%20Impact%20Assessment%20(HRIA)%20commissioned%20for%20India%20in%202022.%20Civil%20society%20groups%20have%20repeatedly%20requested%20Meta%20to%20release%20the%20full%20report%2C%20to%20no%20avail.%20The%20company%20previously%20released%20similar%20reports%20for%20other%20countries%2C%20including%20the%20US%2C%20Myanmar%2C%20and%20Indonesia.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3ENamrata%20Maheshwari%2C%20Asia%20Pacific%20policy%20counsel%20at%20Access%20Now%2C%20said%2C%20%E2%80%9CMeta%20continues%20to%20evade%20responsibility%20by%20not%20releasing%20the%20HRIA%20in%20compliance%20with%20UN%20Guiding%20Principles.%20They%20require%20at%20the%20very%20least%20disclosure%20that%20is%20sufficient%20to%20evaluate%20the%20adequacy%20of%20a%20company%CA%BCs%20response%20to%20the%20human%20rights%20impact.%20Without%20the%20full%20picture%20of%20how%20Meta%CA%BCs%20practices%20and%20policies%20have%20impacted%20human%20rights%20in%20India%20and%20the%20specific%20findings%20and%20recommendations%20in%20the%20HRIA%2C%20it%20is%20impossible%20for%20stakeholders%20%E2%80%93%20governments%2C%20civil%20society%20organisations%2C%20and%20individuals%20%E2%80%93%20to%20effectively%20scrutinise%20Meta%CA%BCs%20policies%20and%20assess%20their%20adequacy.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EAccess%20Now%20said%20it%20was%20alarmed%20by%20Meta%E2%80%99s%20failure%20to%20outline%20a%20clear%20plan%20to%20demonstrate%20election%20preparedness%20in%20India.%20%E2%80%9CMeta%20makes%20no%20mention%20of%20the%20harms%20or%20specific%20issues%20it%20envisages%20for%20elections%20in%20India%2C%20nor%20any%20clear%20and%20structured%20plan%20to%20increase%20meaningful%2C%20inclusive%20engagement%20with%20civil%20society%2C%20and%20the%20ways%20in%20which%20feedback%20will%20be%20incorporated%20to%20mitigate%20harms%2C%E2%80%9D%20it%20said%20in%20a%20statement.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CMeta%20cannot%20continue%20to%20profit%20off%20of%20Indians%20in%20disregard%20of%20their%20human%20rights.%20India%CA%BCs%20400%20million%20Facebook%20users%20need%20to%20know%20whether%20Meta%20has%20taken%20any%20action%20to%20correct%20the%20imbalance%20in%20applying%20its%20practices%20and%20policies%2C%20including%20on%20political%20advertising%2C%20fake%20accounts%2C%20and%20hate%20speech%2C%E2%80%9D%20the%20statement%20adds.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3ERaman%20Jit%20Singh%20Chima%2C%20Asia%20Pacific%20policy%20director%20at%20Access%20Now%2C%20added%20that%20the%C2%A0absence%20of%20any%20mention%20of%20specific%20steps%20that%20Meta%20will%20take%20to%20ensure%20election%20preparedness%20%E2%80%9Cis%20a%20gaping%20hole%E2%80%9D%20in%20the%20report.%20%E2%80%9CThe%20report%20does%20not%20inspire%20confidence%20that%20Meta%20has%20any%20concrete%20plan%20to%20meaningfully%20consult%20with%20civil%20society%20in%20an%20inclusive%20and%20sustained%20manner%20to%20more%20effectively%20tackle%20misinformation%2C%20disinformation%2C%20political%20ads%20and%20hate%20speech%2C%20which%20can%20escalate%20tensions%20during%20elections%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20group%20called%20on%20Meta%20to%20disclose%20the%20full%20findings%20and%20recommendations%20of%20the%20HRIA%20for%20India%2C%20and%20develop%20and%20release%20its%20plan%20to%20tackle%20election-related%20issues%20in%20India.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1695234273000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F05%2F30122835%2FMeta.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Frights%2Fmeta-second-human-rights-report-india-issues-no-plan%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20repor